title: Jacob Holst
text:
Occupation
2022-Present Shift Lead, Walgreens Co.

Took the lead in ensuring photo orders were being completed on time, that supplies were readily available, and that customers were satisfied with their orders; this involved making phone calls with customers on orders not received and with a third party organization to track sendout orders
Exercised problem-solving skills in resolving concerns with pricing mismatches, handling technical problems at the registers, and ensuring proper handling of company proceedures with a focus on customer satisfaction
Trained employees on efficient shelf-stocking practices, keeping a clean workspace, and how to efficiently fill out online and photo orders, including passport photos, canvas prints, and customized merchandise
Took feedback from the store manager and communicated with other members of store leadership to ensure that problems that extended beyond my shift would be appropriately handled

2019 Data Entry, North Park Transportation

Transferred data from shipping bills to a digital format with speed and accuracy
Learned area information to optimize routing and package preparation, becoming familiar with proceedures for handling hazardous materials
